Content: 
The SEO vs GEO debate in 2025 felt like an industry circle jerk.

Each week came with a new acronym and another strategy flip-flop from self-proclaimed "AIO gurus" who were born overnight. The volatility was exasperating.

By 2026, I desperately wanted industry trends grounded in actual data, not echo chambers. 

So, together, Fractl and Search Engine Land analyzed how 75 long-established SEO thought leaders talked about AI-driven search on LinkedIn in 2025. Not to crown a new acronym, but to measure sentiment and consistency amongst a select group of people the industry has come to trust.

What did we learn?

1. AI-era search terms are debated constantly, but we're not rebranding our personal LinkedIn profiles at the same rate. 43% of SEO thought leaders include “SEO” in their LinkedIn headline, compared to 21% who reference “AI” and just 3% who reference “GEO.”

2. Over 70% of posts using AI-related search terms carry a positive tone. We’re not debating IF AI search is the future. We’re just debating what to call it. 

3. 63% of industry leaders reference AIO (AI optimization), and 59% reference GEO (generative engine optimization). These two terms have consistently lead the pack in our research into our evolving SEO industry nomenclature. 

4. The most eye-opening stat was that fewer than 1/3 of our thought leaders maintained consistent usage of AI-related SEO terms and sentiment over the past year. A small group of loud voices drove big swings in their own framing, which creates a major trust gap for anyone trying to follow their lead.

My take?

The solution isn’t to pick a side in the acronym wars. It’s to build content strategies rooted in fundamentals that thrive across organic, social, an AI-driven search platforms: 

✅ SME-backed, data-rich content across the full buyer journey both onsite and offsite 
✅ Robust authority signals in the form of brand research, brand mentions, credible quotes from internal thought leaders and proprietary data 
✅ Repurposing & syndication across the channels your audience already uses

Build timeless strategies that compound entity authority and trust, and you’ll outperform competitors across every meaningful channel. 

